Comments: The additional text occupying 30% of the lower part of the front surface will be applicable as of 01 January 2016. In the meantime, the law requires 100% of the back only.

An amendment of the Cigarettes and other Tobacco Products (Packaging and Labelling) Rules to increase the average size of health warnings on all tobacco packages to 85% was adopted in October 2014 and was scheduled to enter into force on 1 April 2015. However, the date of entering into force has been revoked on 26 March 2015 and is yet to be determined.
